Key Match Events: The Oklahoma City Thunder reached its 28th win on the season on Thursday night versus the LA Clippers.
Oklahoma City routed LA 116-98 en route to its 13th consecutive win.
Amir Coffey led the way for the Clippers with 26 points on the night.
The Thunder's Shai Gilgeous-Alexander and Jalen Williams helped nullify the Clippers' efforts.
Oklahoma City forced 19 turnovers while committing only nine.
Norman Powell and Amir Coffey were primary victims to the Thunder defense, with Powell coughing the ball up six times and Coffey four times.
OKC's starting five dominated the court, averaging a plus-minus of plus-23.4.
The trio of Hartenstein, Williams, and Gilgeous-Alexander posted 58 points.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Clippers snagged 10 more boards than the Thunder—45 to its 35.
Hartenstein grabbed nine boards of his own.
